{
  "text": "This study was conducted between April and November, 2007, in 42 centers, with the approval of the appropriate institutional review boards. Minimal inclusion and exclusion criteria were used in order to diminish the potential selection bias. The 860 enrolled patients received a series of evaluations: clinical global impression improvement/severity (CGI-I/CGI-S), drug dosage, drug compliance, CGI-5 factor [CITATION_1] and patient's satisfaction questionnaire. This evaluation was performed at baseline, at week 2, 4 and then monthly until the end of the study (24 weeks).",
